title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1981-05-02
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw-> Sugaree, El Paso, Bird Song, Cassidy, Candyman-> Minglewood Blues, Althea, Promised Land

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around->Good Lovin'

Set 3

E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
great, until Jerry loses it set 2 Wow, this recording is great, and Set 1 is great.

Set 2 is just a heartbreaker pre Drums.....Jerry starts by forgetting most of the words to Scarlet...and then Fire...and his playing is messed up too, really choppy and weird and angry. I think forgetting so many words just killed all his confidence and made him mad...you can hear it...very rare for 1981. After Estimated he continues messing up Terrapin...wow, he is totally humbled. Must have been hard to witness.

What really blows your mind is the previous and following nights are stellar, as is this tour.

I quit listening after the NFA, which was OK.

I wonder if Jerry pulled it together for the Stella Blue? 81 Stellas are usually pretty great.

I paid $10 at the door This was my first show.  I haven't listened to this recording so I really can't speak to its quality.

The show was 11 stars for me.
